overview: The user initiated a project to implement database storage, an admin
  dashboard, and authentication for a Sleep Questionnaire Application based on a
  provided SOW. The codebase was evaluated, revealing the need for a
   database model, API routes for data saving and
  retrieval (including CSV export), and an admin dashboard. Initially, a custom
  session management system was implemented, but this was later refined to
  leverage Next.js middleware for a simpler and more efficient authentication
  flow. The plan included updating demographic fields, creating Prisma schema,
  implementing API endpoints, and building the admin UI. After implementation,
  the user was guided through database setup (NeonDB, Prisma migrations) and
  browser testing, where a minor issue with form submission via the "Pre-fill &
  Jump to Report" button was identified and resolved by using the "Generate
  Report" button for proper data saving.
